# Build and test

## First-time / clean clone

```bash
bash scripts/bootstrap-third-party.sh
```

## Run tests (preferred — same as CI)

```bash
bash scripts/run-tests.sh          # Linux/macOS
```

```powershell
.\scripts\run-tests.ps1            # Windows
```

## Manual CMake

```bash
cmake -S . -B build -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release -DSTUCKINTHEMD_BUILD_TESTS=ON
cmake --build build
ctest --test-dir build --output-on-failure          # Linux
ctest --test-dir build -C Release --output-on-failure  # Windows/macOS VS
```

Windows VS generator: `-G "Visual Studio 17 2022" -A x64`. If `cmake` is not on PATH, use VS Build Tools CMake under `Common7/IDE/CommonExtensions/Microsoft/CMake/CMake/bin/cmake.exe`.

## Run the app

```powershell
.\build\Release\stuckinthemd.exe [path\to\file.md]
```

## After editing `assets/ui.html`

Re-run **configure** so `ui_embedded.cpp` regenerates: `cmake -S . -B build`, then rebuild.

## External-file / preview tests

`tests/test_app_controller.cpp` — use `sleep_for_mtime()` (~1.1s) around disk writes (Windows mtime granularity).
